## Milestone 2 — Cloud Coin Sync

### Database Schema (Supabase)

```sql
-- Users table (auto-created by Supabase Auth)

-- User profiles (extended data)
CREATE TABLE profiles (
  id UUID REFERENCES auth.users PRIMARY KEY,
  coin_balance INTEGER DEFAULT 3,
  is_pro BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Row Level Security
ALTER TABLE profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users can read own profile" ON profiles FOR SELECT USING (auth.uid() = id);
CREATE POLICY "Users can update own profile" ON profiles FOR UPDATE USING (auth.uid() = id);
```

### Modified Files

#### [MODIFY] [Services/CoinManager.swift](file:///Users/inkalvadodariya/loan_calculator/loan_calculator/Services/CoinManager.swift)
- Add `syncToCloud()` method — pushes local balance to Supabase
- Add `fetchFromCloud()` method — pulls balance from Supabase
- One-time migration: on first sign-in, merge local + cloud coins (take the higher value)
- Fallback to UserDefaults when offline or not authenticated
- Real-time subscription to coin balance changes via Supabase Realtime

---

## Milestone 3 — Saved Calculations & History

### Database Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE saved_calculations (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  calculator_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  inputs JSONB NOT NULL,
  result JSONB NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  is_favorite BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
);

ALTER TABLE saved_calculations ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users can CRUD own calculations" ON saved_calculations
  FOR ALL USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### New Files

#### [NEW] `Services/CalculationStorageService.swift`
- `saveCalculation(name:, viewModel:)` — serializes inputs + results to JSON
- `loadCalculations()` → `[SavedCalculation]`
- `deleteCalculation(id:)`
- `toggleFavorite(id:)`
- Local cache via CoreData/UserDefaults for offline access

#### [NEW] `Models/SavedCalculation.swift`
- `id`, `name`, `calculatorType`, `inputs`, `result`, `createdAt`, `isFavorite`
- `Codable` conformance for Supabase serialization

#### [NEW] `Views/History/HistoryView.swift`
- List of saved calculations grouped by date
- Swipe to delete, tap to restore and view
- Search and filter by calculator type
- Favorite toggle (star icon)
- Empty state for new users

#### [NEW] `Views/History/SaveCalculationSheet.swift`
- Modal presented after viewing results
- Name input field (with auto-suggestion like "Home Loan - Feb 2026")
- Save button → stores to Supabase + local cache

### Modified Files

#### [MODIFY] [HomeView.swift](file:///Users/inkalvadodariya/loan_calculator/loan_calculator/Views/Main/HomeView.swift)
- Add "History" tab/button in toolbar or as a bottom section
- Show recent 3 saved calculations as quick-access cards

#### [MODIFY] [ResultsView.swift](file:///Users/inkalvadodariya/loan_calculator/loan_calculator/Views/Results/ResultsView.swift)
